commit.message:
examples/buffers: Use default filters

* examples/buffers.el (buffers-filter-predicates): Add default filters.

core: Add interactive filters

Co-authored-by: Alex Kost <alezost@gmail.com>

* bui-utils.el (bui-apply-interactive): New function.
* bui-core.el (bui-enable-filter): Use it.
(bui-filter-by-regexp, bui-filter-by-sexp): New functions.
(bui-filter-predicates): Add them.

core: Add 'bui-current-params'

* bui-core.el (bui-current-params): New function.
Fix typo
Fix typos

Update NEWS

I forgot to do it for the last 2 releases :-)
Update version to 1.2.1

list: Call format function with non-void value

This is a followup to commit 995c4c0668cf805af8585d2b2227574014f1b217.

* bui-list.el (bui-list-tabulated-entry): Make sure void value is not
  passed to format function as it breaks backward compatibility too much.

list: Always call format function if it is specified

* bui-list.el (bui-list-tabulated-entry): Move check for a void value
  below the check for a format function.

Remove font-lock keywords for macros

As all macros are highlighted by Emacs since about 24.4.

* bui.el: Remove font-lock keywords.
* bui-core.el: Likewise.
* bui-utils.el: Likewise.

Update version to 1.2.0

This should have been done before "v1.2.0" tag was made on the previous
commit, but well...

list: Improve performance of setting/restoring marks

It is not perfect still, but betten than was.

* bui-list.el (bui-list-current-mark-name): New function.
(bui-list-restore-marks): Use it.
(bui-list-mark-all): Set 'bui-list-marked' at once instead of calling
'bui-list--mark' on each line, although the real problem is calling
'tabulated-list-put-tag' which is left unchanged.

list: Add 'bui-list-map-marked'

* bui-list.el (bui-list-map-marked): New function.
core: Indent 'bui-define-current-args-accessors' macro

utils: Fix typo in a user message

* bui-utils.el (bui-copy-as-kill): add "the" article before "kill ring".

list: Add 'bui-list-marked-or-current'

* bui-list.el (bui-list-marked-or-current): New function.

core: Create buffer only when there are entries to display there

* bui-core.el (bui-get-display-entries-current): Check for entries
  before trying to make a buffer.  If there are no entries, just display
  a message.

core: Display "filtered out" message only if needed

* bui-core.el (bui-show-entries-default): Display the message only when
there were entries before filtering.

core: Introduce 'bui-hint-format' variable

* bui-core.el (bui-hint-format): New variable.
(bui-format-hint-keys): Use it.

utils: Propertize value early in 'bui-split-insert'

* bui-utils.el (bui-split-insert): Propertize VALUE before splitting it
  into strings.  At first, this avoids propertizing list separator (when
  VALUE is a list).  Also this is a performance improvement since a
  simple 'insert' is called instead of 'bui-format-insert'.

utils: Do not propertize list separator in 'bui-get-string'

* bui-utils.el (bui-propertize-maybe): New function.
(bui-get-string): Use it.  Rewrite to avoid propertizing
'bui-list-separator'.
Update version (1.1.0)
Add NEWS

Split hints more

Make more hint variables to allow constructing desired hints of small
pieces.

* bui-core.el (bui-common-hint): Move history keys to...
(bui-history-hint): ... here.  New variable.
(bui-default-hint): Use it.
* bui-list.el (bui-list-common-hint): Remove.  Split into...
(bui-list-mark-hint, bui-list-sort-hint): ... these.  New variables.
(bui-list-hint): Use them.

list: Check global variable to show single entry

* bui-list.el (bui-list-show-single-entry?): Fallback to
  'bui-list-show-single'.

list: Simplify 'desribe' code

* bui-list.el (bui-list-symbol-specifications): Generate
'describe-function' variable by default.
(bui-list-describe-entries): Remove.
(bui-list-describe): Check 'bui-list-describe-function' here.

Simplify mode initializers

* bui-core.el (bui-mode-initialize-default): Deprecate.
(bui-mode-initialize): Call 'bui-mode-initialize-function' if needed.
* bui-info.el (bui-info-initialize): Remove argument, call it from the mode.
* bui-list.el (bui-list-initialize): Likewise.

Add and use 'bui-current-param-title'

* bui-core.el (bui-current-param-title): New function.
* bui-list.el (bui-list-param-title): Remove.
(bui-list-tabulated-sort-key): Use 'bui-current-param-title'.  Remove
'entry-type' argument.
(bui-list-tabulated-format): Likewise.
(bui-list-initialize): Adjust accordingly.

list: Do not use 'format' wrapper

* bui-list.el (bui-list-tabulated-vector): Remove 'entry-type' argument
  and use 'bui-list-format' variable instead of the function.

list: Remove 'sort-key' wrapper

* bui-list.el (bui-list-sort-key): Remove procedure.
(bui-list-tabulated-sort-key): Use 'bui-list-sort-key' variable instead.
